CatDescriptText: Eunice Cook, a nurse, kneels next to a child in a wheelchair while displaying signs for the March of Dimes reading: "Join March of Dimes Mothers March, Thurs Jan 30," and "Fight Birth Defects! March of Dimes, Mothers' March."  The March of Dimes is a voluntary health charity founded in 1938 by U.S. President Franklin Delano Roosevelt (1932-1945) as the National Foundation for Infantile Paralysis to defeat polio.  The organization raised money from school children and others asking them to donate dimes to the cause.
TitMainTitle: Eunice Cook wearing sash inscribed "Mothers March of Dimes," and hat, kneeling next to girl in wheelchair holding March of Dimes placard
